div.h1: TSS: Hardware Ring 3 to Ring 0 Transition Mechanics

g.text: Step 3: CPU Reads TR Register -> Locates TSS
Step 4: CPU Reads SS0 + ESP0 From TSS Memory
Step 5: CPU Pushes Ring-3 State Onto Kernel Stack
Step 6: IDT Handler Address Loaded Into EIP
TRIPLE FAULT: TSS.ESP0 INVALID OR STALE
MANDATORY: Update TSS.ESP0 on Every Context Switch
User PD: indices 0-767 user mappings (U/S=1), 768-1023 kernel (U/S=0)

text.tspan: PIT asserts IRQ0 -> PIC -> CPU INTR pin
Trap gate: IF not cleared on entry

g.text: CPU: CPL=3, gate DPL >= CPL -> ALLOWED

text.tspan: TR = 0x28 (selector loaded by ltr at boot)

g.text: TSS at Physical 0x00108000 (104 bytes, Intel-defined layout)

text.tspan: TSS.ESP0 = kernel stack top for CURRENT process
MUST BE UPDATED ON EVERY CONTEXT SWITCH
CPU now uses the KERNEL stack
iret reversal on return: pops EIP->CS->EFLAGS->ESP->SS
Detects CS.CPL=3 -> switches back to user stack atomically
IDT[32] for IRQ0 | IDT[128] for INT 0x80
Interrupt gate 0x8E: IF cleared on entry

g.text: CPU State After Transition to Ring 0

text.tspan: DPL gate check: user code CANNOT invoke DPL=0 gates
prevents arbitrary ring-0 entry from user mode
TSS.ESP0 points to wrong process kernel stack (stale after context switch)
OR TSS.ESP0 points to unmapped virtual address

g.text: IRQ fires while Process B runs
CPU reads TSS.ESP0 -> still points to Process A stack
CPU pushes frame onto Process A stack (CORRUPTION)
Stack fault handler needs TSS.ESP0 -> another fault
Double Fault -> handler can't push frame -> TRIPLE FAULT
CPU HARD RESET no error message QEMU reboots
Push 5 values to kernel stack: ~10 cycles
ESP = 0x00110FE8 (new ESP after 6 pushes of 4 bytes each)
5. context_switch_asm(old_esp, next_esp, next_cr3) <- iret fires here
Ring-3 code running; interrupt arrives between instructions
CPU accepts interrupt; must find kernel stack via TSS
TR -> GDT[5] -> TSS base address resolved
ESP0 + SS0 loaded from TSS memory
Kernel stack ready; ring-3 state saved; jump to handler
If TSS.ESP0 is stale or invalid -> fault chain
Prevented by always updating TSS.ESP0 before switch
ensures TSS.ESP0 always points to current process kernel stack top
